commit.message:
Support RFC9512 registration for application/yaml Closes #480
https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9512.html

Stop trying to convert Fedora licenses into SPDX

We're living in an SPDX-only world now.

Fixes https://github.com/hughsie/appstream-glib/issues/478

asb-plugin-font: Add glob match for .ttc files

https://docs.fileformat.com/font/ttc/

Found in the wild adding appstream data to the sarasa-gothic-font.

Make the appdata filename check match the plugin globs

This prevents erroring out when processing packages that ship metainfo.xml
files in odd places.
Include screenshot size in "too large" errors
Include screenshot height in "too small" error

asb-plugin-appdata: Never add default icons to firmware, IMs or codecs

Consumers of the appdata file are perfectly capable of adding their own
default icons, and the specification doesn‚Äôt require icons to be present
for any of these component types.

If appstream-builder provides a default icon, software centres cannot
work out whether it‚Äôs provided by the component authors or by
appstream-builder. This means software centres cannot override it with
their own desktop-specific default icons.

Signed-off-by: Philip Withnall <pwithnall@endlessos.org>

See: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-software/-/issues/1483

trivial: Do not expect screenshots from console apps

Initialize proxy resolver in appstream-validate

Oops, trying to use it would just result in criticals.

Fixes #449

Improve handling of <em> and <code> tags

This is still not great code but at least somewhat an improvement. Tests
were expanded to showcase the new behavior.

I think, ideally, we would append opening/closing tags to the ancestor
`p` or `li` node's cdata as soon as we encounter the start/end of an
`em` or `code` element. This would then also handle empty elements
correctly.
